<AbstractNarration>The proposed research will focus on developing computational tools to help connect&lt;br/&gt;ideas from string theory to experimental results from heavy-ion collisions. In particular,&lt;br/&gt;the proposed description of the quark-gluon plasma in terms of the gauge-string duality&lt;br/&gt;will be developed into a more quantitatively predictive framework. Collective flows, hard&lt;br/&gt;probes, and heavy quarkonium systems will be explored in the context of the&lt;br/&gt;gauge-string duality. The results of the proposed research will include explicit&lt;br/&gt;computations based on string theory that should be capable of comparison with data&lt;br/&gt;from the Relativistic Heavy Ion Collider and from the heavy-ion&lt;br/&gt;program planned for the Large Hadron Collider.</AbstractNarration>
